f=Executive Office/vista/operational/agent/vista-config.md · p=Machine-readable configuration vista, scoped strictly what vista's skills actually reference. field below traces real line skill file; nothing speculative. · h2:Config Template=`# --- Roadmap monitoring (roadmap-sync) --- \· roadmap_source: <FILL_IN>          # where the committed roadmap + sprint targets live \· # (file path, board URL, connector) — roadmap-sync Phase 1 \· flag_threshold: <FILL_IN>          # sprints of slip that trigger a flag; skill default is 2 \· # (catalog value) — roadmap-sync Phase 3; change deliberately,` · in=Until `roadmap_source` `metrics_source` filled, roadmap-sync north-star-metric ask operator per-run rather assuming source skill's documented fallback, unchanged file. Until `flag_threshold` filled, roadmap-sync uses built-in default sprints. Until `delivery_owner_contact` filled, flagged-item notifications operator directly. Until `nsm_review_cadence` filled, recurring review assumed exist vista prompts operator set one after first NSM defined. vista's skill set grows something new needs configuring, add what skill actually references. · f=empty/unfilled config equivalent config existing all; never blocks skill running fallbacks.